{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f26832da-a56c-4226-93ae-6620c260f4d1","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\n`dotnet test --filter` uses **VSTest filter syntax** (`&`, `~`). MTP uses a different CLI. Replace with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences after the `--` separator:\n- `&` → **`and`** (logical operator)\n- `~` (contains) stays the same for `FullyQualifiedName`\n- The `--filter` after `--` is the MTP filter flag\n\n### 2. `[Trait]` → `[Category]` attribute\n\nxUnit v3 dropped `Trait(\"Category\", ...)` recognition for filtering. Use the new first-class attribute:\n\n```csharp\nusing Xunit;\n\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]       // was: [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\npublic class IntegrationTests { ... }\n```\n\n### Updated CI command\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3)\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWant me to update your `IntegrationTests.cs` to use the new `[Category]` attribute?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9289b82d-ebe9-4d4a-a954-5cf0afdbd795","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"082B:1F3FEB:84DFAF4:930EE4D:69EABFD3"},"id":"6f775e68-78ae-4766-8154-8cb57005439a","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:56:59.197Z","parentId":"bcf60bec-db9f-4b4f-bc40-0bca79f35fc4"}
